@TrustlessState I'm noticing more consolidation and a reticence to sharing code.

It's likely just the vertical I'm honing in on, but it feels like a lot more teams are being very protective of IP when it comes to mainstream-focused platforms.

This does not mean the tech is not important.

We need to be very thoughtful about decentralization and security.

With this said, the best products will win.

We are entering a phase of web3 where the product matters more than the tech.

Most people will never look under the hood.

All they care about is a seamless onboarding experience.

Make a living by collecting music from artists that you love.

This future is coming much sooner than you think.
